Detailed Description

ObitIOTableAIPS class definition.

This class is derived from the ObitIO class. Related functions are in the ObitIOTableAIPSUtil module.

Usage

Instances of this class are for access to AIPS uv data files. The ObitAIPS class must be initialized before accessing AIPS files; this uses ObitAIPSClassInit. Instances can be made using the newObitIOTableAIPS constructor, or the ObitIOTableAIPSCopy copy constructor and pointers copied (with reference pointer update) using ObitIORef. The destructor (when reference count goes to zero) is ObitIOUnref. This class should seldom need be accessed directly outside of the ObitIO class. Parameters needed (passed via ObitInfoList) are:
  • "BLC" OBIT_int (?,1,1) the bottom-left corner desired as expressed in 1-rel pixel indices. If absent, the value (1,1,1...) will be assumed. dimension of this array is [IM_MAXDIM].
  • "TRC" OBIT_int (?,1,1) the top-right corner desired as expressed in 1-rel pixel indices. If absent, all pixels are included. dimension of this array is [IM_MAXDIM].
  • "IOBy" OBIT_int (1,1,1) an ObitIOSize enum defined in ObitIO.h giving values OBIT_IO_byRow or OBIT_IO_byPlane to specify if the data transfers are to be by row or plane at a time.
  • "Disk" OBIT_int (1,1,1) AIPS "disk" number.
  • "User" OBIT_int (1,1,1) user number.
  • "CNO" OBIT_int (1,1,1) AIPS catalog slot number.

void ObitIOTableAIPSGetFileInfo (  ObitIO *  in,
ObitInfoList *  myInfo,
gchar *  prefix,
ObitInfoList *  outList,
ObitErr *  err
) 
 

Public: Extract information about underlying file.

Parameters:
in Object of interest.
myInfo InfoList on basic object with selection
prefix If NonNull, string to be added to beginning of outList entry name
outList InfoList to write entries into Following entries for AIPS files ("xxx" = prefix):
  • xxxName OBIT_string AIPS file name
  • xxxClass OBIT_string AIPS file class
  • xxxDisk OBIT_oint AIPS file disk number
  • xxxSeq OBIT_oint AIPS file Sequence number
  • xxxUser OBIT_oint AIPS User number
  • xxxCNO OBIT_oint AIPS Catalog slot number
  • xxxDir OBIT_string Directory name for xxxDisk
Following entries for FITS files ("xxx" = prefix):
  • xxxFileName OBIT_string FITS file name
  • xxxDisk OBIT_oint FITS file disk number
  • xxxDir OBIT_string Directory name for xxxDisk
For all File types types:
  • xxxDataType OBIT_string "UV" = UV data, "MA"=>image, "Table"=Table, "OTF"=OTF, etc
  • xxxFileType OBIT_oint File type as "AIPS
For xxxDataType = "Table"
  • xxxTableParent OBIT_string Table parent type (e.g. "MA", "UV")
  • xxxType OBIT_string (Tables only) Table type (e.g. "AIPS CC")
  • xxxVer OBIT_oint (Tables Only) Table version number
err ObitErr for reporting errors.

Public: Open.

The file etc. info should have been stored in the ObitInfoList. For accessing AIPS files the following entries in the ObitInfoList are used:

  • "Disk" OBIT_int (1,1,1) AIPS "disk" number.
  • "User" OBIT_int (1,1,1) user number.
  • "CNO" OBIT_int (1,1,1) AIPS catalog slot number.
  • "TableType" OBIT_string (2,1,1) AIPS Table type
  • "Ver" OBIT_int (1,1,1) AIPS table version number.
